column5: Made it to st charles.Show starts tonight at 5:00.Come on down and talk some fishing with me. Anishinaba Lake booth.

ProV, I'm curious what the mood is at the show, regarding the future of Pheasant Run? From what I read in our local news, they are in the process of shutting-down the facility, with unknown plans for the future.Enjoy your time in my neighborhood, HRG
Mood is good.very busy last night but did here the talk about the show closing at the pheasant run.

They have been operating in the red for awhile. $1,400 -$2,500 for booth is pretty high imo. I think they should find a new venue that could be less for the exhibitors. Although small I liked the Milwaukee show set up.
ProV1800 It was nice to get to meet you and chat with you at the show. It was busy last night and hope the weather stays away for the next couple of days. ILScott
Great meeting up with you and talk about fishing.hope this weather doesnt get to bad so folks cant get to the show.

ProV, It was great meeting you at the show today. Those were some amazing photos of the super clear water you were ice fishing in. It is always nice meeting folks from WC in person that you have traded posts with. If anyone is at the Pheasnt Run All Canada show and want to meet, as always I will be at the Northwinds Canadian Outfitters booth if you want to say hello.
Nice talking to you.ill come by again .lol
